Fees Policy

This Fees Policy sets out the fees payable (a) by sellers for each of their items/products and/or services successfully sold using the Mazadat Platform, regardless of whether such sale is concluded through the Buy Now format or through the Auction format; and (b) by users of the Mazadat Platform subscribing to the Paid Promotions Service provided by Mazadat via the Mazadat Platform.

Mazadat may, from time to time, amend the fees set out under this Fees Policy with immediate effect by posting the changes on the Mazadat Platform and without the need for further notification.

You are solely responsible for reviewing this Fees Policy and shall be liable for all amounts incurred by you in accordance with this Fees Policy.{" "}

All fees

set out under this Fees Policy are exclusive of all applicable taxes and charges.{" "}

In this Fees Policy, terms not defined herein shall have the meanings given to them under the User Agreement.

1. Transaction Fees

Mazadat charges transaction fees, as set out under the User Agreement, to all sellers when their item is successfully sold on the Mazadat Platform, regardless of whether such sale is concluded through the Buy Now format or through the Auction format.

Fees (exclusive of applicable taxes and charges) due and payable by sellers to Mazadat upon the successful sale of new/unused item(s) on the Mazadat Platform are to be calculated as follows:

All used (including defective and damaged) items, regardless of the category to which they belong, successfully sold through the Mazadat Platform shall be subject to a fixed fee payable by the seller and amounting to 10% (exclusive of applicable taxes and charges) of the total sale price of the used item in question.

2. Paid Promotions Fees

Mazadat may offer its users a "Paid Promotions Service", whereby users, wishing to utilize this service, are charged a non-refundable fee to have their ads/listing(s) posted on select locations on the Mazadat Platform in order to increase the visibility of the item(s)/product(s)/service(s) being sold.

Fees payable by users who wish to subscribe to the Paid Promotions Service may either be paid in the form of a one-time payment or a monthly subscription fee depending on the selected package (boost). Fees associated with the Paid Promotions Service vary based on the selected package (boost) as follows:

3. Storage Fees

A daily storage fee (exclusive of applicable taxes and charges), amounting to 10 EGP or 1% of the latest price of the item on the Mazadat Platform, whichever higher, shall be applied and shall be paid by the relevant user in the event that the user fails to pick-up/receive their inventory (including items rejected or returned by a buyer) within (2) calendar days from the date on which the items are received at the relevant Collection Point.
